      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content</head>
         <p>These letters and related materials consisting of seven
         items, 1982 and 1987, were generated by Edward Lay through his
         research concerning a local architect, 
         <persname>Benjamin Charles Baker</persname>(? -1955) of " 
         <corpname>Rosemont</corpname>, " 
         <geogname>Albemarle County, Virginia</geogname>.</p>
         <p>The collection also includes notes taken during a telephone
         conversation with 
         <persname>Henderson Heyward</persname>on June 25, 1987,
         concerning Henderson Heyward, 
         <persname>William L. Bottomley</persname>, 
         <persname>Alfred Llorens</persname>, and Charley Baker.</p>
      </scopecontent>
